\&    say $result\->{data};  # hex string for bare types, hashref for TLV types
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-19 bech32\-encoded entities for human\-friendly display of
Nostr keys, event IDs, and shareable identifiers with metadata.
.PP
These encodings are for display and sharing only. They MUST NOT be used
in NIP\-01 event fields or filters \- use hex format there.
.PP
Uses bech32 (not bech32m) encoding per the NIP\-19 specification.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.IX Header "FUNCTIONS"
All functions are exportable. None are exported by default.
.SS encode_npub
.IX Subsection "encode_npub"
.Vb 1
\&    my $npub = encode_npub($hex_pubkey);
.Ve
.PP
Encodes a 64\-char hex public key as an \f(CW\*(C`npub\*(C'\fR bech32 string.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $npub = encode_npub(\*(Aq7e7e9c42a91bfef19fa929e5fda1b72e0ebc1a4c1141673e2794234d86addf4e\*(Aq);
\&    # npub10elfcs4fr0l0r8af98jlmgdh9c8tcxjvz9qkw038js35mp4dma8qzvjptg
.Ve
.SS decode_npub
.IX Subsection "decode_npub"
.Vb 1
\&    my $hex = decode_npub($npub);
.Ve
.PP
Decodes an \f(CW\*(C`npub\*(C'\fR bech32 string to a 64\-char hex public key. Croaks if
the prefix is not \f(CW\*(C`npub\*(C'\fR.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $hex = decode_npub(\*(Aqnpub10elfcs4fr0l0r8af98jlmgdh9c8tcxjvz9qkw038js35mp4dma8qzvjptg\*(Aq);
\&    # 7e7e9c42a91bfef19fa929e5fda1b72e0ebc1a4c1141673e2794234d86addf4e
.Ve
.SS encode_nsec
.IX Subsection "encode_nsec"
.Vb 1
\&    my $nsec = encode_nsec($hex_privkey);
.Ve
.PP
Encodes a 64\-char hex private key as an \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR bech32 string.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $nsec = encode_nsec(\*(Aq67dea2ed018072d675f5415ecfaed7d2597555e202d85b3d65ea4e58d2d92ffa\*(Aq);
\&    # nsec1vl029mgpspedva04g90vltkh6fvh240zqtv9k0t9af8935ke9laqsnlfe5
.Ve
.SS decode_nsec
.IX Subsection "decode_nsec"
.Vb 1
\&    my $hex = decode_nsec($nsec);
.Ve
.PP
Decodes an \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR bech32 string to a 64\-char hex private key. Croaks if
the prefix is not \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR.
.SS encode_note
.IX Subsection "encode_note"
.Vb 1
\&    my $note = encode_note($hex_event_id);
.Ve
.PP
Encodes a 64\-char hex event ID as a \f(CW\*(C`note\*(C'\fR bech32 string.
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    my $note = encode_note(\*(Aqa\*(Aq x 64);
.Ve
.SS decode_note
.IX Subsection "decode_note"
.Vb 1
\&    my $hex = decode_note($note);
.Ve
.PP
Decodes a \f(CW\*(C`note\*(C'\fR bech32 string to a 64\-char hex event ID. Croaks if
the prefix is not \f(CW\*(C`note\*(C'\fR.
.SS encode_nprofile
.IX Subsection "encode_nprofile"
.Vb 1
\&    my $nprofile = encode_nprofile(pubkey => $hex, relays => \e@relays);
.Ve
.PP
Encodes a profile identifier with optional relay hints using TLV format.
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is required. \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR is optional.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $nprofile = encode_nprofile(
\&        pubkey => \*(Aq3bf0c63fcb93463407af97a5e5ee64fa883d107ef9e558472c4eb9aaaefa459d\*(Aq,
\&        relays => [\*(Aqwss://r.x.com\*(Aq, \*(Aqwss://djbas.sadkb.com\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.SS decode_nprofile
.IX Subsection "decode_nprofile"
.Vb 2
\&    my $data = decode_nprofile($nprofile);
\&    # { pubkey => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, relays => [...] }
.Ve
.PP
Decodes an \f(CW\*(C`nprofile\*(C'\fR bech32 string. Returns a hashref with \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR
and \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR (arrayref, possibly empty). Unknown TLV types are ignored.
.SS encode_nevent
.IX Subsection "encode_nevent"
.Vb 1
\&    my $nevent = encode_nevent(id => $hex, relays => \e@r, author => $hex, kind => $int);
.Ve
.PP
Encodes an event identifier with optional metadata. \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR is required.
\&\f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`author\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR are optional.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $nevent = encode_nevent(
\&        id     => $event_id,
\&        relays => [\*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq],
\&        author => $pubkey_hex,
\&        kind   => 1,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS decode_nevent
.IX Subsection "decode_nevent"
.Vb 2
\&    my $data = decode_nevent($nevent);
\&    # { id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, relays => [...], author => \*(Aq...\*(Aq or undef, kind => N or undef }
.Ve
.PP
Decodes an \f(CW\*(C`nevent\*(C'\fR bech32 string. Returns a hashref. \f(CW\*(C`author\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR are \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not present in the encoding.
.SS encode_naddr
.IX Subsection "encode_naddr"
.Vb 3
\&    my $naddr = encode_naddr(
\&        identifier => $d_tag, pubkey => $hex, kind => $int, relays => \e@r,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Encodes an addressable event coordinate. \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR is optional. Use empty string for
\&\f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR for normal replaceable events.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $naddr = encode_naddr(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-article\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey_hex,
\&        kind       => 30023,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS decode_naddr
.IX Subsection "decode_naddr"
.Vb 2
\&    my $data = decode_naddr($naddr);
\&    # { identifier => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, pubkey => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, kind => N, relays => [...] }
.Ve
.PP
Decodes an \f(CW\*(C`naddr\*(C'\fR bech32 string.
.SS decode_bech32_entity
.IX Subsection "decode_bech32_entity"
.Vb 3
\&    my $result = decode_bech32_entity($bech32_string);
\&    say $result\->{type};  # \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq, \*(Aqnsec\*(Aq, \*(Aqnote\*(Aq, \*(Aqnprofile\*(Aq, \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq, \*(Aqnaddr\*(Aq
\&    say $result\->{data};  # hex string or hashref
.Ve
.PP
Auto\-detects the entity type from the bech32 prefix and decodes it.
For bare types (\f(CW\*(C`npub\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`note\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`data\*(C'\fR is a hex string.
For TLV types (\f(CW\*(C`nprofile\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nevent\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`naddr\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`data\*(C'\fR is a hashref.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $r = decode_bech32_entity(\*(Aqnpub10elfcs4fr0l0r8af98jlmgdh9c8tcxjvz9qkw038js35mp4dma8qzvjptg\*(Aq);
\&    say $r\->{type};  # \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq
\&    say $r\->{data};  # \*(Aq7e7e9c42...\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS encode_nostr_uri
.IX Subsection "encode_nostr_uri"
.Vb 1
\&    my $uri = encode_nostr_uri($bech32_string);
.Ve
.PP
Wraps a NIP\-19 bech32 string with the \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URI scheme (NIP\-21).
Accepts \f(CW\*(C`npub\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`note\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nprofile\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nevent\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`naddr\*(C'\fR.
Croaks if the input is an \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR (private keys must not appear in URIs)
or an unrecognized bech32 prefix.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $npub = encode_npub(\*(Aq7e7e9c42a91bfef19fa929e5fda1b72e0ebc1a4c1141673e2794234d86addf4e\*(Aq);
\&    my $uri = encode_nostr_uri($npub);
\&    # nostr:npub10elfcs4fr0l0r8af98jlmgdh9c8tcxjvz9qkw038js35mp4dma8qzvjptg
.Ve
.SS decode_nostr_uri
.IX Subsection "decode_nostr_uri"
.Vb 3
\&    my $result = decode_nostr_uri($nostr_uri);
\&    say $result\->{type};  # \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq, \*(Aqnote\*(Aq, \*(Aqnprofile\*(Aq, \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq, \*(Aqnaddr\*(Aq
\&    say $result\->{data};  # hex string or hashref
.Ve
.PP
Strips the \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR prefix and decodes the NIP\-19 bech32 entity.
The prefix match is case\-insensitive. Returns the same structure as
\&\f(CW\*(C`decode_bech32_entity\*(C'\fR. Croaks if the URI contains an \f(CW\*(C`nsec\*(C'\fR or
is missing the \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR prefix.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $result = decode_nostr_uri(\*(Aqnostr:npub1sn0wdenkukak0d9dfczzeacvhkrgz92ak56egt7vdgzn8pv2wfqqhrjdv9\*(Aq);
\&    say $result\->{type};  # \*(Aqnpub\*(Aq
\&    say $result\->{data};  # \*(Aq84dee6e676e5bb67b4ad4e042cf70cbd8681155db535942fcc6a0533858a7240\*(Aq
.Ve
